.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-2-7::.
The people prefer 6 different types of sport: climbing, cricket, soccer, golf, lacrosse, tennis
The people use 6 different means of transport: bike, boat, quad-bike, roller, tram, van
1. the person driving the roller is the person driving the roller##1
2. the person driving the van is on the left of the person who's sport is climbing##1
3. the person who's sport is climbing is between the person who's sport is lacrosse and the person who's sport is golf##2
4. the person who's sport is golf is the person driving the van##1
5. the person who's sport is tennis is on the left of the person who's sport is golf##1
6. the person who's sport is lacrosse is between the person driving the roller and the person driving the tram##2
7. the person driving the roller is on the right of the person driving the bike##1
8. the person who's sport is cricket is on the right of the person driving the roller##1
9. the person driving the boat is on the right of the person who's sport is soccer##1

.:: Answer ::.
|             |     1     |   2    |   3   |    4    |     5     |    6    |
| Sport       | tennis | golf | climbing | lacrosse | soccer | cricket |
| Transport   | quad-bike | van    | tram  | bike    | roller    | boat    |

